goals.question: What is the relationship between temperature and pressure?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of temperature vs pressure
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is any correlation between temperature and pressure. If there is a positive correlation, it means that as temperature increases, pressure also increases. If there is a negative correlation, it means that as temperature increases, pressure decreases.

goals.question: What is the distribution of temperature?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the range of temperatures in the dataset and how frequently they occur. It will also help us identify any outliers or unusual patterns in the data.

goals.question: What is the relationship between wind speed and temperature?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of wind vs temperature
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is any correlation between wind speed and temperature. If there is a positive correlation, it means that as temperature increases, wind speed also increases. If there is a negative correlation, it means that as temperature increases, wind speed decreases.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['temperature'], data['pressure'])
    plt.xlabel('Temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Pressure')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between temperature and pressure?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['temperature'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Temperature')
    plt.axvline(data['temperature'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['temperature'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
